modules.description: This module converts between polymorphic variant types (representing codecs, hashes, protocols, and identifiers) and their standardized integer codes or string representations. It maps types like multiaddr, CID, and multihash to integers for binary encoding and decodes them back, while also handling string serialization for interoperability in decentralized systems. These operations enable consistent data identification and protocol negotiation across distributed networks like IPFS and Libp2p.
